  "key_relationships": [
    "ServerHealthService aggregates AlarmService (calls create() for health-check-failure alarms)",
    "ServerHealthService uses kv (Redis) for health status caching with 5s TTL",
    "AlarmService aggregates PagerService (dispatches alerts with severity/fields)",
    "TelemetryService wraps OpenTelemetry NodeSDK as a singleton",
    "TelemetryService integrates with ContextService via pre_arun hook for automatic span wrapping",
    "LogService creates and owns the logger chain; exposes LogContext to consumers",
    "LogContext delegates log() to LogService.log_()",
    "OperationTraceService creates and tracks OperationFrame instances in Context",
    "OperationFrame self-referentially forms parent-child tree",
    "BaseOperation orchestrates OperationFrame lifecycle (PENDING→WORKING→DONE/READY)"
  ],
  "important_notes": "All main services extend BaseService (except OperationTraceService which uses plain constructor). ServerHealthService and AlarmService both have beginDrain() for graceful shutdown. HostDiskUsageService supports macOS and Linux only (Windows TODO). TelemetryService uses a static singleton SDK to prevent double-init. LogService chains multiple logger decorators for buffering, timestamps, and middleware. OperationFrame supports hierarchical effective-status propagation up the parent chain.",
